<br>
For the other skills, though, you would probably do very well for yourself to go ahead and level to 60 first.<br>
<br>
For example, many people are excited about the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> mental clarity</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> skill, with its enhanced mana regeneration. BUT you get an extra point per tick of mana regeneration just from levelling from 55 to 56 anyway, and you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> also</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> get the benefit of new spells and greater spell effectiveness due to being higher level.<br>
<br>
So it would probably be worthwhile to save most of your alternate advancement until after you hit level 60.<br>
<br>
Of course, you are level 52 now, and you may or may not want to hold at that level for a little while. Maybe you have some friends who are not quite up to your level yet and you'd like them to catch up. Or maybe you haven't paid enough visits to Vox and Nagafen for your tastes yet, and since those are level-restricted fights, you would need to hold off at level 52 so you could directly participate in those fights. In those cases, switching your experience bar over would be a good way for you to continue advancing your character without gaining any levels.<br>
<br>
By and large, though, you will get more benefit out of raising your character level than by skilling up in alternate advancement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 185<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/02 7:28:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Alternate Advancement Skills Route</span><hr size=1> I would disagree a little that you get more benefit out of leveling than going the AA route. Reason: As you level, mobs that provide significant experience drop in number. At level 52, one can probably still find mobs blue to you in the Dreadlands, and one pet can eat those for breakfast.<br>
