<BR>Homer's ghost: Whoa whoa whoa. I'm just trying to get in, I'm not running for Jesus.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucydmab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cydmab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#333333>(1/17/02 12:19:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Alternate Advancement Skills Route</span><hr size=1> I've read and heard from people conflicting reports of how hard it is to gain AA vs normal exp. For example, some have reported that doing 10% AA and 90% normal at 59 resulted in roughly EQUAL movement between both exp bars.<br>
<br>
If AA interests you, I'd work toward a level of run speed and see how fast AA advances relative to normal exp for a bit.<br>
<br>
However, I agree mainly with Sarion's conclusion that levels are VERY useful, and many AA skills are somewhat midling in value. For the sake of discussion though, suppose you were level 59 and already had your epic pet, AND I was correct that level 59-60 is about 9 skill points. 'Pose you already had run 3. Then you could either get to level 60 and gain:<br>
<br>
1 hp regen<br>
~40 mana (like finding one small piece of better loot)<br>
Water pet, MS3 (well, the hypothetical mage already has his epic, so he could probally stumble along ok without these)<br>
Mala (good for A-Team single groups, not so critical for exp groups, useful if your guild has very few level 60 shamans on raids, otherwise, not so useful on raids)<br>
10 more points of damage on your level 57 nuke (big whoop)<br>
The level 60 nuke (assuming you have the scroll which is still relatively rare)<br>
Aegis of Ro (convenient, but not necessary, especially if your guild has other level 60 mages)<br>
Banishment (Woo-Hoo! Ya-right)<br>
Super pet heal (assuming you have the super rare scroll)<br>
Ever so slightly better resists, and lower resists on nukes (arguably the biggest benefit)<br>
When noobs do a /who on you it comes up as arch-mage, so they know you are an arch-mage right before they ask you for a port.<br>
<br>
Or with 9 points you could gain, say:<br>
3 hp regen (about worth 1 mana regen with mod rod 2)<br>
Level two arch skill of your choice, or three level 1 arch skills<br>
Much faster gratification and accomplishment over time (since you don't have to &quot;save up&quot; all that exp, but gain benefits as you go)<br>
Get about halfway to /pet hold or your favorite mage class skill<br>
Get the title &quot;Baron&quot; in front of your name<br>
<br>
